column5: Hey all....  I have an open seat for Quinte on Saturday....  I have everything needed... Just need warm DRY clothing... Your lunch... Few bucks for gas...  And a positive attitude towards fishing on a cold windy rainy day... With a fall walleye lunatic... Lol  I'm driving up from Cornwall so I can meet someone anywhere between Cornwall and Kingston along the 401...
Mike I would be all over this if I didn't have plans with the wife.
Mike I would be all over this if I didn't have plans with the wife.  Easy way to fix that Jose, cancel the plans with your wife.  Nice offer Mike, unfortunately I have plans for up north.

Hey mike you might want to check the weather a few more times still calling for very windy conditions tommorow too !!! And quinte can get ugly  and stay that way !!!!! Waves in Lake Ontario were already reported at 5 meters !!!! Yup 15 footers !!!!!!
Don't do it Mike!!!!!! The brutes are still a long ways out. Good luck just the same though.

Supposed to turn to a north wind.... Wich is a cross wind in adolphus reach... If it is north tomorrow it won't be bad... Calling for 20km.... That's just a walleye chop...  I'm checking the weather all day today and making the call tonight....
~~~So I guess Ajax a widdle too far out of the way for a pick up

Like I was saying... I won't be able to go again till the end of november or early December at the earliest if I don't go tomorrow.... And the fall trophy pattern here isn't going yet so I'm not missing out here if I go up tomorrow...
Trip cancel due to high wind forecast.... Gusting 40km/hr in quinte tomorrow...  0-5 km at home... I'll stay here....
